elements.2211.03162_0c0d0df627000fd230262751c622e: While deep reinforcement learning has proven to be successful in solving control tasks, the
elements.2211.03162_b0ef5f1caba9f7250cd94017532eb: nature of an agent has received increasing concerns
elements.2211.03162_79027c822e5d435b9b57e590d7662: , ProtoX, that explains a black-box agent by prototyping the agent's behaviors into scenarios, each represented by a prototypical state
elements.2211.03162_51a0f46ffdc39bff8b9b25b8ee739: When learning prototypes, ProtoX considers both visual similarity and scenario similarity
elements.2211.03162_a0d7d556de3ba99cfc5d19c0fd984: The latter is unique to the reinforcement learning context, since it explains why the same action is taken in visually different states
elements.2211.03162_edaab9d3ebdc22236283bca71cbef: To teach ProtoX about visual similarity, we pre-train an encoder using contrastive learning via self-supervised learning to recognize states as similar if they occur close together in time and receive the same action from the black-box agent
elements.2211.03162_19267810746766f828bcd747c89a7: We then add an isometry layer to allow ProtoX to adapt scenario similarity to the downstream task
elements.2211.03162_16dd66ba6ba3e258ae22f64707887: ProtoX is trained via imitation learning using behavior cloning, and thus requires no access to the environment or agent
elements.2211.03162_c59d413d6e99ac419853e82aeb9b4: In addition to explanation fidelity, we design different prototype shaping terms in the objective function to encourage better interpretability
elements.2211.03162_d185536828296eb6a18cbaf6b8047: We conduct various experiments to test ProtoX
elements.2211.03162_c6d7ce8b283f3633822a620360bbf: Results show that ProtoX achieved high fidelity to the original black-box agent while providing meaningful and understandable explanations.
elements.2211.03162_d7ce39e7b371ab3a0435dee341402: Deep reinforcement learning (DRL) has been widely used to solve various control problems such as autonomous driving
elements.2211.03162_0b62f18f6e0acc8950714d695b7b6: Despite superior performance, DRL agents are often criticized for being
elements.2211.03162_aa709e2b2257a4d9ea09c0111e644: in nature and unable to provide human-understandable explanations for their actions
elements.2211.03162_dc5aebee94c584a03b791eeda85fc: Popular solutions to interpreting a black-box agent include attention-based methods
elements.2211.03162_4399dc910b173d17390d7f6c926ba: These explanations, however, only inform users of where the agent
elements.2211.03162_7b666d20ee95cb521fdf6918f4273: , but do not provide a more specific explanation for
elements.2211.03162_31f4d3c559ce61062683ae8b06b12: Some recent methods answer this question by formulating a classification problem and building a decision tree from state information to predict an action
elements.2211.03162_e5f3f63adb5d305bc2732974fc783: However, tree-based models face the limitation of feature representation, that they can only work with meaningful features in order to make sense to humans
elements.2211.03162_4fcf98b8f750d1ab8963a9bc32151: They do not naturally apply to unstructured data such as images and texts unless human-understandable information is manually extracted
elements.2211.03162_8288a6f0b79bd340866ee7511295b: a black-box agent that works with unstructured data
elements.2211.03162_557414e716d23bf336e82da5bc37f: To make the explanations understandable, we make use of the concept of
elements.2211.03162_5405ffe10d2d25b6ed76471d579ec: from recent DNN models for image classification
elements.2211.03162_7c095b6905080c8dbd8a559fcbcb1: A prototype is an instance (e.g. an image) from data that is representative of a prominent feature for a certain class
elements.2211.03162_937b8013aed71c3a3f64ba56582b3: For example, the red-bellied woodpecker class could have a prototype for its red head and a prototype for its wings with a zebra-like pattern, etc
elements.2211.03162_2eef80ddb6329d0fd41184525a54d: Then, when there is a new input, the input can be compared against all prototypes trained from data
elements.2211.03162_7db64b2328e5c7ba8337930fae9ef: If the input also has a red head and zebra-like pattern on the wings, the weighted sum of similarities in the red-bellied woodpecker class will be high, and thus the input will be predicted to be in this class.
elements.2211.03162_832464d45e7b5415f877b5257694f: In this paper, we propose a policy explainer called ProtoX, which explains an action by relating an input state to a set of prototypical behaviors learned from the demonstrations from the agent
elements.2211.03162_29085a5ecda406715e2d8ae1cb6d9: shows an example of ProtoX explanation for an agent playing the Super Mario game
elements.2211.03162_2cf467b54adb6d5281acd1fd9e322: ProtoX learns a set of prototypical states during training, which are most representative of the agent's behavior
elements.2211.03162_0ba32e2c25a61ac295c0160e67d21: In summary, ProtoX prototypes an agent's behavior into a small set of representative behavior patterns, each represented by a prototype, and explains the agent's action based on these basic patterns
elements.2211.03162_7fad543d84770075ae82fef6b5238: Therefore, a key determinant of the success of ProtoX is the prototypes
elements.2211.03162_e3259bd4258411f22b3c0fa28fa09: An important consideration when computing the similarity between an input and a prototype is the
elements.2211.03162_9d3b135345737d0a5a8e5ffd4efcd: Our definition of similarity must appropriately balance the aspects of visual and contextual similarity
elements.2211.03162_1c41fad110481ca594084a4d5e06c: Otherwise, e.g. if two states look entirely different and are assigned high similarity, human users may get confused and discredit the explanation
elements.2211.03162_a64c0f58098ab8bd32433cc95957b: In ProtoX, we design a self-supervised training step for the encoder to learn visual similarity
elements.2211.03162_bbdcaeb782602ec9875274fad37cf: Usually, images that are closer to each other in time and receive the same actions are more visually similar than those far away or receiving different actions
elements.2211.03162_fa6e6c8c2ceb6dced22af4600db2e: Thus, we create a siamese net
elements.2211.03162_37d1814ab52a4824e8e5fb16a5f53: that utilizes a modified form of the time-contrastive loss
elements.2211.03162_b8ad150ca440a71b37e8828874b5d: Our pre-training routine yields encoders whose feature spaces cluster together visually similar states which occur closely in time and have the same corresponding actions
elements.2211.03162_cf396cc24d51ab36b6e4179938d85: In the supervised learning setting, visual similarity would be the only consideration, given the nature of image classification tasks
elements.2211.03162_b41c9073a9635441b3bf877d827d6: However, in a reinforcement learning setting, two visually similar states could receive different actions (such as the flip points we define later), and two visually dissimilar states could represent a similar
elements.2211.03162_5b0c93b3a15fe16e93a93db0f6886: Therefore, the similarities need also need to take into account
elements.2211.03162_7b6486c74b96016f6bfd470f29842: Here, a scenario represents a collection of states in which an agent performed the same action for similar reasons
elements.2211.03162_81da676c4f07a1d9425de4dc3b73c: , an action RIGHT+JUMP has a high similarity score to prototypes that represent different scenarios for jumping, which could be that Mario encounters a pipe (the 1st prototype), a hole (the 3rd prototype), or preparing to hit a question mark brick (the 2nd prototype)
elements.2211.03162_9c99a8dd148a09e162063f3c4045b: In fact, the scenario similarity brings more value to the explanation, since it helps users to think about what is common between two visually dissimilar states that leads to the same action
elements.2211.03162_7a8b99f3f5d6eeaf1135b133532ef: To allow the feature representations to incorporate scenario similarity, we add a near-isometry layer after the encoder, which applies a linear transformation of the output of the encoder to allow some states to move closer to each other
elements.2211.03162_cdec6facc7bbbdcfb050bcbd6d519: ProtoX is trained end-to-end via imitation learning, by learning from the demonstrations of the black-box agent to be explained
elements.2211.03162_ffab45819beb21e1beb60c3e222ba: in this paper because it requires minimal information from both the agent and the environment: only demonstrations from the agent and no access to the environment or the agent
elements.2211.03162_d6bd2babd28f1dd0b8cd9bd8c423f: Therefore, it is most applicable in practice
elements.2211.03162_bc31d9d9c6149e2813816529d67a8: Many other imitation methods, such as GAIL-based methods and inverse reinforcement learning methods, require more information from the environment or/and the agent, such as knowing the transition functions, executing a policy during training, etc
elements.2211.03162_b96c82bfb771012717ea521f4eb5f: We summarize the contributions of ProtoX
elements.2211.03162_a115e74fa852d13e9902948c8ac52: Most importantly, the reinforcement learning agent is used as a black-box, which means ProtoX only needs to learn from demonstrations and does not need to access the internals of the agent, which makes it easier to use in practice
elements.2211.03162_ce34e7d52a47935b4bcd21217a113: Meanwhile, ProtoX also does not need to access or interact with the environment
elements.2211.03162_ec29e5fc766ad76d4515947053c9e: Second, we design an encoder to preserve visual similarity for better interpretability via self-supervised learning and an isometry layer
elements.2211.03162_cdd5ec5ea22224ca51d7533abaf71: It allows ProtoX to adapt to both visual and contextual notions of similarity
elements.2211.03162_94521acba8b7a9efb93ff25eaac26: Third, while the existing interpretable baseline (VIPER) only works well on structured data, ProtoX can more naturally work with unstructured data.
elements.2211.03162_f77bd86cbe1dc27ee5183e79950c6: RL interpretation can be categorized into two main groups: inherently interpretable RL models and post-hoc explanation approaches
elements.2211.03162_bbd018b177b58393e8614dd20c3cc: Inherently interpretable RL models generate policies that are intrinsically understandable, such as Neurally Directed Program Search
elements.2211.03162_ab82d7cabbafebf1189d3ac739cfe: , or extract time step importance within episodes as strategy-level explanations
elements.2211.03162_8e31934d3ea71f8f8049895528fb2: Post-hoc methods, like the proposed ProtoX, aim to explain a given black-box agent to help users understand the agent's decision-making process towards an action
elements.2211.03162_33d384eea3bf8397ed01e3899868f: The goal is not good task performance but high fidelity in explaining a given black-box agent, regardless of the own performance of the agent
elements.2211.03162_d37608305d4c458885f92176d01f0: Based on the type of data they work with, post-hoc methods can also be split into two areas
elements.2211.03162_8bf14b51faf9e925c513e320b4380: The first class of methods only work with structured data, such as genetic programming
elements.2211.03162_e13833bdc9606cb52597f55a5eb51: These methods often adopt existing forms of interpretable models from supervised learning, such as rules
elements.2211.03162_f832d4c245ac32185a3f053739421: However, since the explanations need to directly use state features, they do not naturally work with unstructured data
elements.2211.03162_db98eac2f1f7545dbf5f4ea08f8ff: To learn video games from pixels, they require meaningful features to be extracted
elements.2211.03162_d00507e58a68558510f7fa2ad9170: The other type of post-hoc methods work with structured data
elements.2211.03162_aed49282acd55f7849a00aa6b2559: The explanations, however, are either only at the global level or too abstract, such as saliency maps that only inform users of where the agent
elements.2211.03162_8ccc43a6e6347f5f3a17db7e8323e: but do not directly explain the policy
elements.2211.03162_7e70de95095b109f6b7655bcf9a86: Another stream of work that aims to provide some interpretability stem from the family of imitation learning
elements.2211.03162_27c761c0f0f7ecae99f926af31d05: For example, inverse reinforcement learning (IRL) methods
elements.2211.03162_305afc1f4eee02310d18d68f79cf5: aim at learning a reward function under which the observed demonstrations of an agent is near-optimal
elements.2211.03162_3923de9b4ddafdd4313eaee7c4cba: The interpretability, however, is only achieved through the learned reward function with a pre-defined structure (e.g., linear combination of state features) rather than understanding the policy itself
elements.2211.03162_361b472f869883bcfbb8006a50cbb: Methods based on generative adversarial imitation learning (GAIL)
elements.2211.03162_6ba4ee11095e9db1501e0845f9ade: provide indirect explanations to the learned policy in terms of global and local feature importance or latent factors that govern the policy generation
elements.2211.03162_c83fd8c82731b9cc92fdce16d588b: However, none of them provide a direct explanation of the expert's actions under each state that are intuitive to humans
elements.2211.03162_a312a932cbeaef40ea2a43995fe83: More importantly, all of the above methods require intensive interactions with the environment or the agent during training (such as executing a policy), which are often not accessible in most practical situations
elements.2211.03162_d143a7cc88f11d9361abe128eebe1: On the other hand, our proposed ProtoX model is completely offline and requires no environment or agent interaction
elements.2211.03162_9267ae6448d0bbc2d04b28257dfa1: It also needs no additional information from the environment such as the transition function, reward function, etc
elements.2211.03162_5ee3e6a80dce4b9fca7749f2ab4e3: Another work that is relevant to ProtoX is VINN
elements.2211.03162_ef874149a3605f04a1626ecf6b80f: , which also learns from visual demonstrations.

elements.2211.03162_79680b6979d99682b5c62d300be45: Since VINN was not designed as an explainer, it does not consider the visual similarity and the human-understandable explanation as ProtoX does.

elements.2211.03162_fa99b0940da0a68621513b54a920e: We propose a prototype-based policy explainer, ProtoX, for explaining black-box reinforcement learning agents
elements.2211.03162_6a34cbcd432c73092345cb279a962: ProtoX explains an agent by prototyping its behavior into different scenarios, each represented by a prototype
elements.2211.03162_041115fa412ecd971d86b8f0edf2a: ProtoX explains an action by comparing the corresponding input with its prototypes, computing the similarity scores between the inputs and prototypes, and then calculating accumulated evidence for each action
elements.2211.03162_37f00e3f017bd26625190fc91f7be: ProtoX takes into account both visual similarity and scenario similarity
elements.2211.03162_e04cdcd2a02a198ae06931083efb5: We use self-supervised training and contrastive learning to learn the notion of visual similarity from expert demonstrations, and allow ProtoX to learn scenario similarity by using an isometry layer during its behavior cloning training
elements.2211.03162_ab58f35dbce4bc7fc8b0d0813e093: Results show that ProtoX achieved high fidelity compared to VIPER, a black-box model with similar network architecture, and also a GAIfO model whose policy network had a similar architecture.
elements.2211.03162_1fb3a89c49497865c75baebb11e5d: The interpretation of the prototypes requires a basic understanding of the task
elements.2211.03162_04f00a7b7589b6ff4bd44370c3c75: For example, to interpret the prototype for UP in Figure
elements.2211.03162_f4aa835670fc207720fd2cb54cfe7: users need to know the basic logic for playing the game, and thus can comprehend why the submarine goes up in that scenario
elements.2211.03162_7bf9bd37f4a7561336acfdf515da1: In addition, we have also noticed in the Seaquest game that the expert anticipates the arrival of enemies and shoots at them before they even enter the screen
elements.2211.03162_2651bd55658b45a47ae0ad397258b: Thus, ProtoX learns prototypes showing the expert shooting at nothing
elements.2211.03162_18f21975c315da3178e18c4041df5: ProtoX's mode of interpretation does not inform the users of such anticipatory behavior
elements.2211.03162_29e48a1175daab4fde81aad55c424: One would not be able to understand such prototypes without a basic understanding of the game
elements.2211.03162_a25d29d0f25aab80ca68e4df1d5e9: Also, ProtoX may learn similar and redundant prototypes
elements.2211.03162_019ce7202ed34ece897fb5e95c76d: Some pruning techniques could be created to further improve the quality of prototypes.
